00:00:01.034 --> 00:00:02.802 line:5%,start
ABBY (VOICEOVER):
Previously, on "Dance Moms."

00:00:02.869 --> 00:00:04.004 line:5%,start
'Cause you're not really on the team.

00:00:04.070 --> 00:00:05.572 line:5%,start
I'm on this team.

00:00:05.638 --> 00:00:06.740 line:5%,start
Well, you weren't on the team back then.

00:00:06.806 --> 00:00:07.807 line:5%,start
But I am now.

00:00:07.874 --> 00:00:09.542 line:5%,start
I don't know what we're
going to do with her now.

00:00:09.609 --> 00:00:10.844 line:5%,start
Aw.

00:00:12.045 --> 00:00:13.480 line:5%,start
What are you here for?

00:00:13.546 --> 00:00:15.048 line:5%,start
For Asia to dance with the team,
or to learn from Abby?

00:00:15.115 --> 00:00:16.883 line:5%,start
She did amazing in last week's crew.

00:00:16.950 --> 00:00:18.151 line:5%,start
Asia's already proved herself.

00:00:18.218 --> 00:00:20.353 line:5%,start
What I'm telling you is between you and I.

00:00:20.420 --> 00:00:22.555 line:5%,start
Right now, you are hurting my daughter.

00:00:22.622 --> 00:00:24.657 line:5%,start
I more a part of this team
than you will ever be.

00:00:24.724 --> 00:00:28.294 line:5%,start
When opportunity comes knocking,
you better take advantage of it.

00:00:28.361 --> 00:00:29.396 line:5%,start
Shame on you.

00:00:30.797 --> 00:00:32.332 line:5%,start
ABBY (VOICEOVER):
Coming up on "Dance Moms."

00:00:32.399 --> 00:00:33.733 line:5%,start
So is Abby here?

00:00:33.800 --> 00:00:35.402 line:5%,start
- I don't know.
ABBY (ON PHONE): Gianna?

00:00:35.468 --> 00:00:36.970 line:5%,start
Abby?

00:00:37.037 --> 00:00:39.506 line:5%,start
One, two, three, Gia's girls.

00:00:39.572 --> 00:00:41.441 line:5%,start
- You're a fill-in.
- No, I'm here.

00:00:41.508 --> 00:00:44.878 line:5%,start
I texted her, and she said
you will be fired from this dance studio

00:00:44.944 --> 00:00:46.179 line:5%,start
if you choreograph that dance.

00:00:46.246 --> 00:00:47.981 line:5%,start
I don't care where the [bleep] she works.

00:00:48.048 --> 00:00:49.582 line:5%,start
Whoa, oh, oh.

00:00:49.649 --> 00:00:51.885 line:5%,start
She has made it clear she doesn't care

00:00:51.951 --> 00:00:53.753 line:5%,start
about our kids or her team.

00:00:53.820 --> 00:00:55.522 line:5%,start
Brooke, there's nothing we can do.

00:00:55.588 --> 00:00:56.656 line:5%,start
[sniffling]

00:00:56.723 --> 00:00:58.458 line:5%,start
Don't cry.
Come on.

00:00:58.525 --> 00:01:00.693 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:01:00.760 --> 00:01:03.263 line:5%,start
[theme music playing]

00:01:03.329 --> 00:01:06.599 line:95%,end
Get up, get on the floor.

00:01:06.666 --> 00:01:09.436 line:95%,end
My world is with my girls.

00:01:09.502 --> 00:01:12.639 line:95%,end
Living on the dance floor.

00:01:12.705 --> 00:01:15.075 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:01:19.512 --> 00:01:21.848 line:95%,end
Hi, G. Oh, it's cold in here.

00:01:21.915 --> 00:01:23.216 line:95%,end
Good morning.

00:01:23.917 --> 00:01:24.951 line:95%,end
GIANNA: Good morning, guys.
- Hi.

00:01:25.018 --> 00:01:26.820 line:95%,end
Good morning.

00:01:26.886 --> 00:01:28.688 line:95%,end
GIANNA: Hey, girl.
- Where's your friend?

00:01:28.755 --> 00:01:29.956 line:95%,end
Not here yet.

00:01:30.023 --> 00:01:31.057 line:95%,end
Ooh.

00:01:31.758 --> 00:01:34.427 line:95%,end
- Hi, Gia.
GIANNA: Hi. Good morning.

00:01:35.361 --> 00:01:37.530 line:95%,end
- Hello, Gia.
GIANNA: Hi.

00:01:37.597 --> 00:01:39.833 line:5%,start
I walk into the studio,
and Gia's sitting at the front desk,

00:01:39.899 --> 00:01:42.769 line:5%,start
and I just assume that Abby's
at a headband sale somewhere.

00:01:43.403 --> 00:01:45.071 line:95%,end
- Yeah.
- Where's Ab, I wonder.

00:01:45.138 --> 00:01:47.540 line:95%,end
I don't know. I asked Gianna, I was like
hey, you're here by yourself.

00:01:47.607 --> 00:01:49.075 line:95%,end
She was, yeah, Abby's not here yet.

00:01:49.142 --> 00:01:51.811 line:95%,end
Over the past three days
Mrs. Miller has not been well.

00:01:52.912 --> 00:01:54.414 line:95%,end
- Oh, you're kidding.
- Mnm-mnm.

00:01:54.481 --> 00:01:58.251 line:5%,start
Abby's mom is very, very ill,
and getting sicker and sicker

00:01:58.318 --> 00:02:00.186 line:95%,end
by the day.

00:02:00.253 --> 00:02:02.589 line:95%,end
But it's not like Abby not to show up,

00:02:02.655 --> 00:02:04.991 line:95%,end
so I'm really concerned that
something's really wrong.

00:02:05.058 --> 00:02:07.360 line:95%,end
- So is Abby here?
- I don't know.

00:02:07.427 --> 00:02:09.429 line:95%,end
Is she going to come and
help with the rehearsal?

00:02:09.496 --> 00:02:11.931 line:95%,end
- Hey, Ab. It's Gia.
- And Rachel.

00:02:11.998 --> 00:02:13.800 line:95%,end
Just wondering where you were.

00:02:13.867 --> 00:02:18.404 line:95%,end
We have to order costumes
for the group dance in 44 minutes now,

00:02:18.471 --> 00:02:21.174 line:95%,end
because they're coming from St. Louis,
and there's a holiday tomorrow. So--

00:02:22.809 --> 00:02:25.712 line:5%,start
--we don't know where you are,
but we hope you're on the way.

00:02:25.778 --> 00:02:28.581 line:5%,start
If Abby doesn't show up today,
I don't know what I'm going to do.

00:02:28.648 --> 00:02:31.684 line:5%,start
She has to pick costumes
and assign solos.

00:02:31.751 --> 00:02:33.086 line:95%,end
I can't make those decisions without her.

00:02:33.153 --> 00:02:34.854 line:95%,end
She doesn't have to tell us
all of her personal details,

00:02:34.921 --> 00:02:36.256 line:95%,end
but if she's not going
to be here for pyramid,

00:02:36.322 --> 00:02:39.392 line:95%,end
it's just professionalism, that's all.
She has a business.

00:02:39.459 --> 00:02:42.362 line:95%,end
And it's not being harsh or cruel, just--

00:02:42.929 --> 00:02:45.131 line:95%,end
I don't really know anything though,
so I don't have anything to tell them.

00:02:45.198 --> 00:02:48.101 line:95%,end
- Right.
- And so there's no pyramid today.

00:02:48.168 --> 00:02:50.370 line:95%,end
Maybe you should start the group part,
since you know there's a group.

00:02:50.436 --> 00:02:52.305 line:95%,end
That's what I said.

00:02:52.372 --> 00:02:53.640 line:5%,start
- We need to cut it out.
- There she is.

00:02:53.706 --> 00:02:54.741 line:95%,end
GIANNA: Hi, guys.
- Hi.

00:02:54.807 --> 00:02:55.808 line:5%,start
Did you hear from Abby?

00:02:55.875 --> 00:02:57.210 line:5%,start
Okay. When you and Gia met.

00:02:57.277 --> 00:02:59.512 line:95%,end
I'm just going to start the group.
I have the group music.

00:02:59.579 --> 00:03:01.014 line:95%,end
- Oh.
WOMAN: That's good.

00:03:01.080 --> 00:03:02.282 line:95%,end
It's called "Just Be."

00:03:02.348 --> 00:03:05.451 line:95%,end
It's pretty lyrical, it's not hard.

00:03:05.518 --> 00:03:07.320 line:95%,end
- And James is here to help me.
WOMAN: Oh.

00:03:07.387 --> 00:03:08.621 line:95%,end
So--

00:03:08.688 --> 00:03:10.256 line:95%,end
WOMAN: Do you know where
we're going this weekend?

00:03:10.323 --> 00:03:14.794 line:95%,end
No. But wherever we're going, we have
to have a group dance, so--

00:03:14.861 --> 00:03:15.995 line:95%,end
- So true.
- Okay.

00:03:16.062 --> 00:03:17.797 line:95%,end
- Come on.
- All right.

00:03:17.864 --> 00:03:21.167 line:95%,end
Work hard, girls.
Be safe. Thank you, Gianna.

00:03:21.234 --> 00:03:23.903 line:5%,start
HOLLY: Still no Abby, but at least
we have Gia and James,


00:03:23.970 --> 00:03:25.672 line:5%,start
and they are Abby's best teachers.

00:03:25.738 --> 00:03:29.075 line:5%,start
And we also have a group song,
so I guess that's a start.

00:03:29.142 --> 00:03:31.344 line:95%,end
You guys do realize Abby's not here.

00:03:31.411 --> 00:03:32.879 line:95%,end
We don't know when she's coming.

00:03:32.946 --> 00:03:34.681 line:95%,end
I brought James in
special to help me today

00:03:34.747 --> 00:03:37.483 line:95%,end
because Abby's least not here.
Please pay attention.

00:03:37.550 --> 00:03:39.786 line:95%,end
You guys give Abby that respect,
so please give us that respect.

00:03:39.852 --> 00:03:40.954 line:95%,end
- Okay?
GIRLS: Okay.

00:03:41.020 --> 00:03:42.622 line:95%,end
Do we know the theme?
We don't know the theme.

00:03:42.689 --> 00:03:44.023 line:95%,end
The theme is called, "abandoned".

00:03:44.090 --> 00:03:47.560 line:95%,end
- Stop.
- What? It's true, we're abandoned.

00:03:47.627 --> 00:03:48.795 line:95%,end
- It's not called abandoned.
- It's all right.

00:03:48.861 --> 00:03:52.932 line:95%,end
It's called, "I left you on
the steps of a fire station

00:03:52.999 --> 00:03:54.734 line:95%,end
in the little basket.
You're abandoned."

00:03:54.801 --> 00:03:58.338 line:95%,end
Abby always talks about loyalty
and dedication to the team,

00:03:58.404 --> 00:04:01.007 line:95%,end
and here are these kids
working their butts off,

00:04:01.074 --> 00:04:04.811 line:95%,end
and their teacher doesn't even
have the decency to show up.

00:04:04.877 --> 00:04:06.379 line:95%,end
I think the kids are fine with no pyramid.

00:04:06.446 --> 00:04:08.948 line:95%,end
However, I think they want
to know who's doing what.

00:04:09.015 --> 00:04:10.116 line:95%,end
Yeah, I agree with that.

00:04:10.183 --> 00:04:14.087 line:95%,end
Who's doing a solo,
where the heck are we going,

00:04:14.153 --> 00:04:17.757 line:95%,end
who are we going to go up
against, what what's going on?

00:04:17.824 --> 00:04:19.259 line:95%,end
I mean, that's what we
like pyramid most is--

00:04:19.325 --> 00:04:20.760 line:95%,end
- Right.
- --is to find out--

00:04:20.827 --> 00:04:21.861 line:95%,end
--it's an information session.

00:04:21.928 --> 00:04:22.929 line:95%,end
--what's happening.

00:04:22.996 --> 00:04:24.964 line:95%,end
Gia said that she was working
on the group dance, but what

00:04:25.031 --> 00:04:26.633 line:95%,end
about the other dances?

00:04:26.699 --> 00:04:28.701 line:95%,end
You think Abby will give Gia the authority

00:04:28.768 --> 00:04:30.470 line:95%,end
to pass out solos and duets?

00:04:30.536 --> 00:04:32.705 line:95%,end
I don't think Gianna
would do anything on her own

00:04:32.772 --> 00:04:34.007 line:95%,end
without checking with Abby.

00:04:34.073 --> 00:04:36.109 line:95%,end
No, I don't either.
Maybe there aren't any, don't know.

00:04:37.243 --> 00:04:39.445 line:95%,end
WOMAN: Okay, who do you think has solos?

00:04:39.512 --> 00:04:40.680 line:95%,end
I think Payton's going to do a solo, too.

00:04:40.747 --> 00:04:41.848 line:95%,end
I think it's going to
be Payton and Maddie.

00:04:41.914 --> 00:04:43.816 line:95%,end
- Oh, maybe it will be Payton.
- I think Patton and Maddie.

00:04:43.883 --> 00:04:45.718 line:95%,end
We all want our kids to have solos.

00:04:45.785 --> 00:04:47.520 line:95%,end
Maddie hasn't had a solo in weeks,

00:04:47.587 --> 00:04:49.322 line:95%,end
Payton hasn't had a solo the entire time

00:04:49.389 --> 00:04:51.658 line:95%,end
she's been on the team,
Kristie Ray threatened

00:04:51.724 --> 00:04:53.960 line:95%,end
to quit last week if Asia
didn't get a solo.

00:04:54.027 --> 00:04:55.595 line:95%,end
If Abby doesn't assign these solos

00:04:55.662 --> 00:04:57.997 line:95%,end
I really hope that Gia can
handle the wrath of the mother

00:04:58.064 --> 00:04:59.565 line:95%,end
of whoever doesn't get one.

00:04:59.632 --> 00:05:01.768 line:95%,end
I just want Asia to dance,
that's why I'm here.

00:05:01.834 --> 00:05:03.469 line:95%,end
I want her to dance,
that's why we're here.

00:05:03.536 --> 00:05:04.604 line:95%,end
That's what we all want.

00:05:04.671 --> 00:05:06.039 line:95%,end
I don't blame you Kristie, though.

00:05:06.105 --> 00:05:07.974 line:95%,end
If you're not getting what
you want you got to fly.

00:05:08.041 --> 00:05:11.110 line:95%,end
So wait, you're saying that she should
have a solo in the group every week?

00:05:11.177 --> 00:05:15.114 line:95%,end
She's done two weeks in a row, ma-zing
in of groups. She deserves a solo.

00:05:15.181 --> 00:05:17.750 line:95%,end
Asia hadn't trained with us all summer,

00:05:17.817 --> 00:05:19.052 line:95%,end
never came to camp--

00:05:19.118 --> 00:05:20.486 line:95%,end
So, you went with Candy Apple.

00:05:20.553 --> 00:05:23.890 line:5%,start
I think out of all the girls,
Asia is the last person

00:05:23.956 --> 00:05:25.558 line:5%,start
that should have a solo this week.

00:05:25.625 --> 00:05:27.860 line:95%,end
She's only had a million already,

00:05:27.927 --> 00:05:29.862 line:95%,end
and Asia's not here all the time.

00:05:29.929 --> 00:05:32.665 line:95%,end
Asia's going to work-- let
me get let me get this straight to you.

00:05:32.732 --> 00:05:36.069 line:95%,end
Asia's going to work, and take jobs,
and train whenever she can.

00:05:36.135 --> 00:05:37.303 line:95%,end
So if you have a problem with that--

00:05:37.370 --> 00:05:39.272 line:95%,end
- I don't have a problem with that.
- Well, obviously you do.

00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:41.474 line:95%,end
You just said, you weren't here,
so you have a problem with it.

00:05:41.541 --> 00:05:43.076 line:95%,end
If you're telling me that you--

00:05:43.142 --> 00:05:45.078 line:95%,end
Did you not hear me say--

00:05:45.144 --> 00:05:46.713 line:95%,end
I didn't hear you because you're--

00:05:46.779 --> 00:05:49.415 line:95%,end
--I had a problem with
where she was on the pyramid.

00:05:49.482 --> 00:05:51.250 line:95%,end
I don't care where the [bleep] she works.

00:05:51.317 --> 00:05:53.486 line:95%,end
- Excuse me?
- Now did you hear me?

00:05:53.553 --> 00:05:55.088 line:95%,end
Whoa, oh, oh.

00:05:55.154 --> 00:05:56.456 line:95%,end
- Why did you say it?
- Look at.

00:05:56.522 --> 00:05:59.325 line:95%,end
- Jill dropped the F bomb.
- You're screwed in the head

00:05:59.392 --> 00:06:02.161 line:95%,end
No, you're a hot mess, because
now you're dropping F bombs.

00:06:02.228 --> 00:06:04.597 line:95%,end
Well, okay, I think you're a hot mess.

00:06:04.664 --> 00:06:06.666 line:95%,end
You only get mad when you're wrong.

00:06:06.733 --> 00:06:08.534 line:5%,start
Nope.

00:06:08.601 --> 00:06:11.304 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:06:11.371 --> 00:06:14.107 line:5%,start
GIANNA: The group routine
this week is called "Just Be."

00:06:14.173 --> 00:06:16.442 line:5%,start
I'm going to keep it very
simple, very elegant.

00:06:16.509 --> 00:06:18.277 line:95%,end
James is a very unique choreographer,

00:06:18.344 --> 00:06:20.246 line:95%,end
and I'm so excited that he
is helping me this week.

00:06:20.313 --> 00:06:22.615 line:95%,end
And hopefully Abby will be
appreciative, and not fire me

00:06:22.682 --> 00:06:24.016 line:95%,end
for doing our own choreography.

00:06:24.083 --> 00:06:26.319 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:06:26.386 --> 00:06:28.855 line:95%,end
Let me see it now,
without Asia and Mackenzie.

00:06:28.921 --> 00:06:30.189 line:95%,end
[telephone ringing]

00:06:30.256 --> 00:06:32.091 line:95%,end
- Who are you calling?
- I'm calling Kelly.

00:06:32.158 --> 00:06:33.693 line:95%,end
- Why?
- Because.

00:06:33.760 --> 00:06:35.828 line:95%,end
[telephone ringing]
I don't know owe you an explanation.

00:06:35.895 --> 00:06:37.430 line:95%,end
No, you don't.
But I think it's rude.

00:06:37.497 --> 00:06:39.031 line:95%,end
- Kelly?
KELLY (ON PHONE): Hello?

00:06:39.098 --> 00:06:40.700 line:5%,start
- Hi.
CHRISTI: Hi, Kel.

00:06:40.767 --> 00:06:41.968 line:95%,end
KELLY (ON PHONE): Hi.

00:06:42.034 --> 00:06:45.872 line:95%,end
I'm just calling to let you
know that Abby is not here.

00:06:45.938 --> 00:06:48.775 line:95%,end
I don't know where she is but anyhow,


00:06:48.841 --> 00:06:50.243 line:95%,end
the girls are learning a group dance

00:06:50.309 --> 00:06:53.679 line:95%,end
and since you made your statement
that you're back on the team--

00:06:53.746 --> 00:06:56.282 line:95%,end
LESLIE (ON TV): Like Rosa Parks,
I'm not moving.

00:06:56.349 --> 00:06:58.384 line:95%,end
KELLY (ON TV): I'm either
sitting there, or I'll go home

00:06:59.152 --> 00:07:00.219 line:95%,end
LESLIE (ON TV): Bye.

00:07:01.087 --> 00:07:03.055 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: I don't know if you
have plans for your girls

00:07:03.122 --> 00:07:05.191 line:95%,end
to dance this week, but if you do

00:07:05.258 --> 00:07:08.194 line:95%,end
or if you want them to learn the dance,
I would suggest that you--

00:07:08.261 --> 00:07:09.862 line:95%,end
WOMAN: Come on down.
- --get here.

00:07:10.696 --> 00:07:12.598 line:5%,start
CHRISTI: All right.
I'll talk to you later.

00:07:12.665 --> 00:07:15.168 line:95%,end
Kelly can come back right
now because Abby's not here

00:07:15.234 --> 00:07:17.170 line:95%,end
so she's not facing that
big fight at the front door

00:07:17.236 --> 00:07:19.238 line:95%,end
and her girls can come and dance,

00:07:19.305 --> 00:07:21.808 line:95%,end
which is all Kelly really
wanted in the first place.

00:07:21.874 --> 00:07:23.776 line:95%,end
Christi, what makes you
think you have the right

00:07:23.843 --> 00:07:26.045 line:95%,end
to invite Kelly and the kids
back here, when Abby is just--

00:07:26.112 --> 00:07:27.547 line:95%,end
- I-- I didn't invite her.
- -- away for the moment?

00:07:27.613 --> 00:07:30.516 line:95%,end
I was telling her what was going
on as far as I'm concerned,

00:07:30.583 --> 00:07:32.251 line:95%,end
those kids were still on the pyramid,

00:07:32.318 --> 00:07:33.619 line:95%,end
they're still part of this team.

00:07:33.686 --> 00:07:35.221 line:95%,end
I'm giving her the information.

00:07:35.288 --> 00:07:36.556 line:95%,end
What she does with it is up to her.

00:07:36.622 --> 00:07:38.558 line:95%,end
- But your name is not Abby.
CHRISTI: I didn't say it was.

00:07:38.624 --> 00:07:39.926 line:95%,end
She did not allow them back on the--

00:07:39.992 --> 00:07:40.993 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: [inaudible].

00:07:41.060 --> 00:07:42.361 line:95%,end
--you're really crossing the line, here.

00:07:42.428 --> 00:07:44.030 line:95%,end
Does anybody think I'm crossing the line?

00:07:44.096 --> 00:07:46.232 line:95%,end
Uh, no, I don't, but Abby might.

00:07:46.299 --> 00:07:48.734 line:95%,end
I don't think Kelly should come in here,
because I think Abby would freak.

00:07:48.801 --> 00:07:50.736 line:95%,end
MELISSA: I understand why Kristie thinks

00:07:50.803 --> 00:07:53.606 line:95%,end
now is a good time for Kelly to bring her
girls back onto the team.

00:07:53.673 --> 00:07:56.909 line:95%,end
I mean, she knows how upset Abby
would be if she brought back

00:07:56.976 --> 00:07:59.078 line:95%,end
her kids without permission.

00:07:59.145 --> 00:08:00.947 line:95%,end
If Gia and James don't want them in there,

00:08:01.013 --> 00:08:03.015 line:95%,end
they're going to tell him to leave, so--

00:08:03.082 --> 00:08:04.116 line:95%,end
Gia knows better to--

00:08:04.183 --> 00:08:05.218 line:95%,end
I don't think Abby's
expecting it to happen, so--

00:08:05.284 --> 00:08:06.619 line:95%,end
--to do that.

00:08:06.686 --> 00:08:07.987 line:95%,end
--I'm sure she didn't cover this with Gia.

00:08:08.054 --> 00:08:09.322 line:95%,end
Gia's not going to know what to do.

00:08:09.388 --> 00:08:11.357 line:95%,end
[music playing]
- She might not even come.

00:08:11.424 --> 00:08:13.359 line:95%,end
- Right.
- We may be worrying about nothing.

00:08:14.160 --> 00:08:15.595 line:95%,end
KELLY: I always come back to this studio

00:08:15.661 --> 00:08:17.797 line:95%,end
because my girls miss their family.

00:08:17.864 --> 00:08:19.432 line:95%,end
These girls are like sisters.

00:08:19.532 --> 00:08:22.535 line:95%,end
They have been together since
they were three years old.

00:08:22.602 --> 00:08:26.339 line:5%,start
And as much as Abby doesn't like it,
we are part of this team.

00:08:26.405 --> 00:08:29.742 line:5%,start
I'm just really not looking forward
to talking to that woman.

00:08:29.809 --> 00:08:31.811 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:08:31.878 --> 00:08:33.145 line:95%,end
Excuse me.

00:08:33.212 --> 00:08:34.981 line:95%,end
My kids are here to learn the group dance.

00:08:35.047 --> 00:08:36.148 line:95%,end
GIANNA: Okay.

00:08:36.215 --> 00:08:38.751 line:95%,end
I'm already stressed out enough
with Abby not showing up,

00:08:38.818 --> 00:08:40.453 line:95%,end
and now Kelly walks in the door.

00:08:40.520 --> 00:08:43.222 line:95%,end
If I stop Kelly from entering, it'll
be a huge blow out with the moms,

00:08:43.289 --> 00:08:45.258 line:95%,end
and I don't have time for that.

00:08:45.324 --> 00:08:46.592 line:95%,end
WOMAN: Ah!

00:08:46.659 --> 00:08:47.994 line:95%,end
Ah! [clapping]

00:08:48.628 --> 00:08:49.629 line:95%,end
GIRL: Boom!

00:08:50.897 --> 00:08:53.466 line:95%,end
KELLY: Well, hello.
WOMAN: [interposing voices]

00:08:53.533 --> 00:08:54.867 line:95%,end
- Ah.
- New carpet.

00:08:54.934 --> 00:08:56.002 line:95%,end
Where you sitting?

00:08:56.068 --> 00:08:57.169 line:95%,end
WOMAN: - Doesn't smell
good, but I'm getting by--

00:08:57.236 --> 00:08:58.538 line:95%,end
What are you moving over for?
My seat's over here.

00:08:58.604 --> 00:08:59.639 line:95%,end
I'm not moving.

00:08:59.705 --> 00:09:01.974 line:95%,end
LESLIE: Payton has earned
her spot on this team.

00:09:02.408 --> 00:09:04.176 line:5%,start
Being on the elite competition team

00:09:04.243 --> 00:09:07.280 line:5%,start
is a great opportunity for any dancer,

00:09:07.346 --> 00:09:10.216 line:95%,end
and Kelly is not going to take
that away from my daughter.

00:09:10.283 --> 00:09:14.620 line:95%,end
I just want Payton to feel welcomed here,

00:09:14.687 --> 00:09:16.455 line:95%,end
and not feel awkward and uncomfortable.

00:09:16.522 --> 00:09:19.058 line:95%,end
And I have not done anything to make
Payton feel uncomfortable.

00:09:19.125 --> 00:09:20.693 line:95%,end
You just showing up makes
her feel uncomfortable.

00:09:20.760 --> 00:09:22.361 line:95%,end
- Well, that's not my problem.
- Do you blame her, though?

00:09:22.428 --> 00:09:23.462 line:95%,end
KELLY: No.

00:09:23.529 --> 00:09:25.231 line:95%,end
Every time you did show up,
she was kicked back off the team.

00:09:25.298 --> 00:09:26.933 line:95%,end
It's Abby's decision.

00:09:26.999 --> 00:09:28.501 line:95%,end
KELLY: I don't pick who
gets to be on the team.

00:09:28.568 --> 00:09:30.136 line:95%,end
- But it's not going to change.
- So she should be upset with Abby--

00:09:30.202 --> 00:09:31.537 line:95%,end
LESLIE: It's not going to change--
- --not me.

00:09:31.604 --> 00:09:32.705 line:95%,end
LESLIE: --again, so you're
going to walk back in here.

00:09:32.772 --> 00:09:33.839 line:95%,end
But that's not my fault.

00:09:33.906 --> 00:09:36.309 line:95%,end
I think Leslie is just very desperate

00:09:36.375 --> 00:09:37.710 line:95%,end
to be part of this team.

00:09:37.777 --> 00:09:43.115 line:95%,end
But Abby continues to tell her, you're not
part of the team, you're filling in.

00:09:43.182 --> 00:09:45.284 line:95%,end
When Abby comes in yelling,
this is between you two.

00:09:46.018 --> 00:09:47.119 line:95%,end
She keeps saying it's my fault.

00:09:47.186 --> 00:09:48.354 line:95%,end
[laughs]

00:09:48.421 --> 00:09:50.189 line:95%,end
I think it's your fault.
I think you guys are starting

00:09:50.256 --> 00:09:51.824 line:95%,end
trouble and it's unnecessary.

00:09:51.891 --> 00:09:54.660 line:95%,end
I told Abby I was coming back to the team,
at the competition.

00:09:54.727 --> 00:09:55.728 line:95%,end
LESLIE: But she's not here.

00:09:55.795 --> 00:09:56.996 line:95%,end
I don't care.

00:09:57.063 --> 00:09:58.297 line:95%,end
LESLIE: But If she is here--

00:09:58.364 --> 00:09:59.865 line:95%,end
KELLY: When she is here,
I will still be sitting here.

00:09:59.932 --> 00:10:01.701 line:95%,end
If she was here she would
probably have you removed.

00:10:02.568 --> 00:10:03.603 line:95%,end
She can try.

00:10:03.669 --> 00:10:05.638 line:95%,end
[music playing]


00:10:07.807 --> 00:10:09.875 line:5%,start
HOLLY: Hello..
GIANNA: Good morning.

00:10:09.942 --> 00:10:11.677 line:95%,end
HOLLY: You're by yourself again?

00:10:11.744 --> 00:10:12.912 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:10:12.979 --> 00:10:14.013 line:95%,end
[telephone ringing]

00:10:14.080 --> 00:10:15.314 line:95%,end
ABBY (ON TELEPHONE): Gianna?

00:10:15.381 --> 00:10:16.816 line:95%,end
Abby.

00:10:17.850 --> 00:10:19.185 line:5%,start
[telephone beeping]

00:10:19.251 --> 00:10:20.353 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:10:20.419 --> 00:10:21.854 line:95%,end
Guys, she's not coming.

00:10:21.921 --> 00:10:23.623 line:95%,end
I guess that answers my question.

00:10:23.689 --> 00:10:25.891 line:5%,start
I was just going to ask you, is she here?

00:10:25.958 --> 00:10:29.762 line:5%,start
Now, the first day of not having
Abby present was pretty good.

00:10:29.829 --> 00:10:31.430 line:95%,end
It's like having a substitute teacher,

00:10:31.497 --> 00:10:33.532 line:95%,end
you're really happy about that.

00:10:33.599 --> 00:10:35.401 line:95%,end
Day two, I'm not too sure.

00:10:35.468 --> 00:10:37.536 line:95%,end
She needs to come home,
she needs to do her job.

00:10:38.437 --> 00:10:40.439 line:95%,end
GIRLS: Hello.
- Hi.

00:10:40.506 --> 00:10:41.874 line:95%,end
Kids, you want to come
in and start stretching?

00:10:41.941 --> 00:10:43.042 line:95%,end
GIRLS: Yes.

00:10:43.109 --> 00:10:44.143 line:95%,end
Moms, why don't you guys come in too

00:10:44.210 --> 00:10:46.412 line:95%,end
so I can tell you a little
bit about this weekend.

00:10:46.479 --> 00:10:47.647 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:10:47.713 --> 00:10:49.682 line:5%,start
After Abby hung up on me,
I got a text from her

00:10:49.749 --> 00:10:50.916 line:5%,start
about this week's competition.

00:10:50.983 --> 00:10:53.786 line:5%,start
I guess whatever Abby is going through
this week she doesn't want to talk.

00:10:53.853 --> 00:10:55.855 line:95%,end
As you guys know, Abby's still not here.

00:10:55.921 --> 00:10:57.256 line:95%,end
I don't know if she's coming.

00:10:57.323 --> 00:10:58.991 line:95%,end
I don't know if she's coming back today.

00:10:59.058 --> 00:11:01.861 line:5%,start
I really don't think it's fair
what Abby's doing to Gianna.

00:11:01.927 --> 00:11:03.462 line:5%,start
She left her high and dry.

00:11:03.529 --> 00:11:06.365 line:5%,start
Gianna is just stepping in and making
sure that these kids are

00:11:06.432 --> 00:11:09.201 line:95%,end
getting what they need this week
because Abby doesn't care to do it.

00:11:09.268 --> 00:11:11.771 line:95%,end
I tried to call her, she hung up on me.

00:11:11.837 --> 00:11:14.907 line:95%,end
Did Abby give you any instructions
about this week, at all?

00:11:14.974 --> 00:11:17.543 line:95%,end
We're going to Believe Talent Competition,
in San dusky, Ohio.

00:11:17.610 --> 00:11:19.779 line:95%,end
[applause]

00:11:19.845 --> 00:11:21.580 line:95%,end
It's a fun one.
It's a good one.

00:11:21.647 --> 00:11:23.182 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:11:23.249 --> 00:11:24.917 line:95%,end
As far as I know, all nine of you

00:11:24.984 --> 00:11:26.452 line:95%,end
are going to be in the
group dance this week.

00:11:26.519 --> 00:11:28.154 line:95%,end
JILL: Nine kids.

00:11:28.220 --> 00:11:31.257 line:5%,start
That's a lot, so Gianna has
her work cut out for her.

00:11:31.323 --> 00:11:33.459 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:11:33.526 --> 00:11:36.462 line:95%,end
Asia, you're having a solo this week.

00:11:36.529 --> 00:11:38.564 line:95%,end
[applause]

00:11:38.631 --> 00:11:41.233 line:95%,end
It's a jazz routine, called "Lightning."

00:11:41.300 --> 00:11:42.902 line:5%,start
Asia has a solo, and she should.

00:11:42.968 --> 00:11:45.471 line:5%,start
She has not lost once
in the solo category.

00:11:45.538 --> 00:11:48.207 line:95%,end
And the second solo is Maddie.

00:11:48.274 --> 00:11:49.675 line:95%,end
[applause]

00:11:49.742 --> 00:11:52.044 line:95%,end
Those are all the
routines that Abby gave me.

00:11:52.111 --> 00:11:55.081 line:95%,end
Because there's only three numbers,
and we usually have four,

00:11:55.147 --> 00:11:57.850 line:95%,end
is there any way I could have a solo?

00:11:57.917 --> 00:12:00.252 line:95%,end
- Have you asked Abby?
- No.

00:12:00.319 --> 00:12:02.354 line:95%,end
Gianna announces that
there's only three dances,

00:12:02.421 --> 00:12:05.958 line:5%,start
and normally we take
four, and Abby's not here,

00:12:06.025 --> 00:12:09.895 line:95%,end
so I just feel like this is a perfect
opportunity for Brooke to ask for a solo.

00:12:09.962 --> 00:12:11.697 line:95%,end
We can maybe work something out,

00:12:11.764 --> 00:12:14.767 line:95%,end
but I can't do anything
without talking to her first.

00:12:14.834 --> 00:12:16.335 line:95%,end
You know what?

00:12:16.402 --> 00:12:19.538 line:95%,end
If Abby comes back and she takes it away
from her, I'm fine with that.

00:12:19.605 --> 00:12:21.140 line:95%,end
But at least Brooke tried.

00:12:21.207 --> 00:12:25.177 line:5%,start
The night hides changes,

00:12:25.244 --> 00:12:28.447 line:95%,end
Rearranges--

00:12:28.514 --> 00:12:30.049 line:95%,end
GIANNA: Asia, your feet.

00:12:30.116 --> 00:12:31.383 line:95%,end
I want this to--

00:12:31.450 --> 00:12:35.588 line:95%,end
You know, I can't really say I'm all that
sad Abby's not here.

00:12:35.654 --> 00:12:37.223 line:95%,end
Saying that you miss
Abby when she's not here

00:12:37.289 --> 00:12:40.159 line:95%,end
is like saying you miss a hemorrhoid.
Do you really?

00:12:40.226 --> 00:12:42.495 line:95%,end
- I'm sad for her mom--
- Very much.

00:12:42.561 --> 00:12:44.430 line:95%,end
--but But I'm disappointed
that Abby doesn't call us.

00:12:44.497 --> 00:12:45.531 line:95%,end
We don't know.

00:12:45.598 --> 00:12:46.665 line:95%,end
Well, she did the same
thing with Broadway Baby.

00:12:46.732 --> 00:12:48.701 line:95%,end
I know, but did she
hang up on Gia, really?

00:12:48.768 --> 00:12:50.069 line:95%,end
- Yeah, she did.
- Well, she told us she did.

00:12:50.136 --> 00:12:51.637 line:95%,end
[interposing voices]
- Leslie was there with me.

00:12:51.704 --> 00:12:53.539 line:95%,end
I think she's always been there for Gia,

00:12:53.606 --> 00:12:55.708 line:95%,end
so she's really going through
a lot with her mother for her

00:12:55.775 --> 00:12:57.710 line:95%,end
not to even take Gia's phone calls.

00:12:57.777 --> 00:13:00.346 line:95%,end
All we want is a phone call.
Where are you?

00:13:00.446 --> 00:13:02.882 line:95%,end
Are you coming back? But nothing.
No word.

00:13:02.948 --> 00:13:04.517 line:95%,end
0 from Abby.

00:13:04.583 --> 00:13:06.519 line:95%,end
I was there when Abby was
on the phone with Gianna,

00:13:06.585 --> 00:13:08.587 line:95%,end
and just as easily as she could have said,

00:13:08.654 --> 00:13:11.490 line:95%,end
Hello, make sure you run the
group dance, I can't make it,

00:13:11.557 --> 00:13:13.092 line:95%,end
instead she hung up.

00:13:13.159 --> 00:13:15.561 line:95%,end
That's not professional
and it's not responsible.

00:13:15.628 --> 00:13:17.029 line:95%,end
Give her a brief explanation.

00:13:17.096 --> 00:13:19.665 line:95%,end
Something's come up, I can't
make it, take care of the group

00:13:19.732 --> 00:13:21.333 line:95%,end
dance and the two solos.

00:13:21.400 --> 00:13:23.402 line:95%,end
- No, three solos.
- Three solos?

00:13:23.469 --> 00:13:24.737 line:95%,end
Oh.

00:13:24.804 --> 00:13:26.405 line:95%,end
- How about you?
- That's a surprise.

00:13:26.472 --> 00:13:27.573 line:95%,end
- How about you?
- That's right.

00:13:27.640 --> 00:13:28.707 line:95%,end
I would've been the same way--
[interposing voices]

00:13:28.774 --> 00:13:31.877 line:95%,end
Yeah. Kelly, can I just say, I would
take baby steps if I were you.

00:13:31.944 --> 00:13:33.512 line:95%,end
Yeah, I know.
You're pretty gutsy.

00:13:33.579 --> 00:13:35.447 line:95%,end
Any one of those kids
could've asked for a solo,

00:13:35.514 --> 00:13:36.916 line:95%,end
they just didn't raise their hand.

00:13:37.516 --> 00:13:39.084 line:95%,end
Okay, it has to look like that on stage,

00:13:39.151 --> 00:13:40.920 line:95%,end
please, please, please,
please, please, please.

00:13:40.986 --> 00:13:42.655 line:95%,end
This is the first time
we're going to a competition

00:13:42.721 --> 00:13:44.290 line:95%,end
without Abby, and it's a really big deal.

00:13:44.356 --> 00:13:46.258 line:95%,end
It's going to be tough,
but I think we can do it.

00:13:46.325 --> 00:13:48.093 line:5%,start
GIRLS: One, two, three.

00:13:49.628 --> 00:13:51.463 line:5%,start
GIANNA: Okay, you're done.


00:13:51.530 --> 00:13:53.299 line:95%,end
GIRLS: Thank you.

00:13:53.365 --> 00:13:55.534 line:95%,end
Is Abby with her mother?

00:13:55.601 --> 00:13:57.136 line:95%,end
I don't know.

00:13:57.203 --> 00:13:58.871 line:95%,end
Well, you are the only
one who speaks to her.

00:13:58.938 --> 00:14:00.172 line:95%,end
Why don't you find out?

00:14:00.239 --> 00:14:02.041 line:5%,start
Obviously, Abby is with her mother.

00:14:02.107 --> 00:14:03.175 line:95%,end
I'll call her.

00:14:03.242 --> 00:14:04.810 line:95%,end
LESLIE: It would probably be
better if Melissa called her.

00:14:04.877 --> 00:14:07.613 line:95%,end
Abby is probably in L.A.
scouting a new studio to get

00:14:07.680 --> 00:14:09.081 line:95%,end
away from these crazy moms.

00:14:09.148 --> 00:14:10.950 line:95%,end
I'd like to be a fly on the wall

00:14:11.016 --> 00:14:14.019 line:95%,end
when she looks down and sees
your name on her caller ID.

00:14:14.086 --> 00:14:16.088 line:95%,end
I have a sneaky suspicion that Abby

00:14:16.155 --> 00:14:19.058 line:95%,end
is off with that creepy werewolf
guy that she has been seeing.

00:14:19.124 --> 00:14:20.492 line:95%,end
[telephone ringing]

00:14:20.559 --> 00:14:22.461 line:95%,end
WOMAN (ON PHONE): At the tone,
please record your message.

00:14:22.528 --> 00:14:23.796 line:95%,end
[beeping]

00:14:23.863 --> 00:14:25.531 line:95%,end
Hi, Abby it's Kelly.

00:14:25.598 --> 00:14:27.766 line:95%,end
I just wanted to let you
know that we had asked Gianna

00:14:27.833 --> 00:14:29.969 line:95%,end
if Brooke was able to do a solo,

00:14:30.035 --> 00:14:32.571 line:95%,end
and she said we had to get
approval from you first.

00:14:32.638 --> 00:14:34.673 line:95%,end
So if you could give Gianna a call

00:14:34.740 --> 00:14:36.408 line:95%,end
and let her know if she's allowed or not,

00:14:36.475 --> 00:14:37.576 line:95%,end
I would appreciate it.

00:14:37.643 --> 00:14:39.011 line:95%,end
Thanks, bye.

00:14:39.078 --> 00:14:41.480 line:95%,end
HOLLY: The only thing
I wish I could see Abby's face

00:14:41.547 --> 00:14:42.815 line:95%,end
when she gets that message.

00:14:42.882 --> 00:14:45.784 line:95%,end
You know what you guys, I am
not going to let her scare me.

00:14:45.851 --> 00:14:47.052 line:95%,end
She doesn't scare me.

00:14:47.119 --> 00:14:50.022 line:95%,end
I can handle whatever Abby wants
to do with me, I don't care.

00:14:50.089 --> 00:14:51.123 line:95%,end
GIANNA: Hey, girl.

00:14:51.190 --> 00:14:52.324 line:95%,end
Ready?

00:14:52.391 --> 00:14:53.626 line:95%,end
When I talked to Abby last,
she was talking

00:14:53.692 --> 00:14:55.861 line:95%,end
about your emotions,
and she said every week

00:14:55.928 --> 00:14:57.696 line:95%,end
she sees the same face.

00:14:57.763 --> 00:15:00.699 line:95%,end
So she gave me this piece of
music that is so powerful,

00:15:00.766 --> 00:15:01.800 line:95%,end
we need to pull more out.

00:15:01.901 --> 00:15:03.102 line:95%,end
More emotion.

00:15:03.168 --> 00:15:04.637 line:95%,end
I need more connection
with the audience,

00:15:04.703 --> 00:15:06.672 line:95%,end
not the same old face. Okay?

00:15:07.773 --> 00:15:09.675 line:95%,end
Maddie is performing a
lyrical or routine this week

00:15:09.742 --> 00:15:11.010 line:95%,end
to "Holding On." [music playing]

00:15:11.076 --> 00:15:12.645 line:95%,end
It's a very emotional piece.
[music playing]

00:15:12.711 --> 00:15:14.546 line:95%,end
I know that Abby says
she hasn't been connecting

00:15:14.613 --> 00:15:16.448 line:5%,start
with the audience recently,
so I'm making sure

00:15:16.515 --> 00:15:18.784 line:5%,start
that this is extra emotional,
that she can give something

00:15:18.851 --> 00:15:20.786 line:95%,end
more than just a typical Maddie solo.

00:15:20.853 --> 00:15:23.055 line:95%,end
More. Because--

00:15:23.122 --> 00:15:24.857 line:95%,end
Good.

00:15:24.924 --> 00:15:27.192 line:95%,end
So you guys know that my kids
are involved in the Starlight

00:15:27.259 --> 00:15:28.460 line:95%,end
Foundation--
- Uh-huh.

00:15:28.527 --> 00:15:30.262 line:95%,end
--and this little girl--

00:15:30.329 --> 00:15:32.898 line:95%,end
I was going to invite her to
come watch because she said

00:15:32.965 --> 00:15:35.834 line:95%,end
that our kids inspire her.

00:15:35.901 --> 00:15:37.636 line:95%,end
[phone ringing]

00:15:39.271 --> 00:15:40.472 line:5%,start
Hi, Laurie it's Melissa.

00:15:40.539 --> 00:15:41.640 line:95%,end
Hello.

00:15:41.707 --> 00:15:42.708 line:5%,start
LORI (ON PHONE): Hello, everyone.

00:15:42.775 --> 00:15:43.876 line:5%,start
- Hello.
- Hi.

00:15:43.943 --> 00:15:46.745 line:95%,end
So we wanted to see
if you and your daughter

00:15:46.812 --> 00:15:49.048 line:95%,end
can come to the studio tomorrow, and come

00:15:49.114 --> 00:15:50.649 line:95%,end
to the competition on Saturday?

00:15:54.253 --> 00:15:56.255 line:5%,start
- Oh, that's so great.
WOMAN: Great.

