group dance without Abby,

00:39:09.280 --> 00:39:11.349 line:95%,end
and they beat really good dancers.

00:39:11.415 --> 00:39:13.984 line:95%,end
[screams]

00:39:15.619 --> 00:39:17.121 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:39:17.188 --> 00:39:18.389 line:95%,end
That was like winning the Olympics.

00:39:18.456 --> 00:39:20.524 line:95%,end
That is really-- it's a big deal.

00:39:20.591 --> 00:39:21.826 line:95%,end
[cheering]

00:39:21.892 --> 00:39:24.128 line:95%,end
I definitely think that
Abby will be back next week,

00:39:24.195 --> 00:39:26.430 line:95%,end
unless her mother takes
a turn for the worst.

00:39:26.497 --> 00:39:27.832 line:95%,end
Call her right now and tell her we won.

00:39:27.898 --> 00:39:29.266 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:39:29.333 --> 00:39:31.001 line:95%,end
Are you serious?
Do I really need to call her?

00:39:31.068 --> 00:39:32.970 line:95%,end
She probably doesn't
want to hear about our win.

00:39:33.037 --> 00:39:34.839 line:95%,end
[phone ringing]

00:39:37.541 --> 00:39:38.642 line:95%,end
I'm sorry?

00:39:42.012 --> 00:39:43.381 line:5%,start
Is Abby there?

00:39:46.250 --> 00:39:47.651 line:5%,start
- [laughs]
- Okay.

00:39:47.718 --> 00:39:49.587 line:95%,end
Can you just tell her that the group won.

00:39:49.653 --> 00:39:50.988 line:5%,start
MANDY (ON PHONE): The group won.

00:39:51.055 --> 00:39:53.557 line:5%,start
And Maddie won, and Asia won.

00:39:53.624 --> 00:39:55.292 line:95%,end
How's Mrs. Miller feeling?

00:39:57.561 --> 00:39:59.296 line:95%,end
Okay. She's not the hospital, is she?

00:40:00.765 --> 00:40:01.766 line:95%,end
Okay.

00:40:01.832 --> 00:40:04.435 line:95%,end
I'm really not sure where Abby is.

00:40:04.502 --> 00:40:06.370 line:95%,end
Is she in Pittsburgh, is she in Florida?

00:40:06.437 --> 00:40:08.739 line:95%,end
She was with her mother, but
then when she called Gianna,

00:40:08.806 --> 00:40:09.940 line:95%,end
she wasn't with her mother at all.

00:40:10.007 --> 00:40:11.175 line:95%,end
That's all hearsay, though.

00:40:11.242 --> 00:40:12.777 line:95%,end
You don't know if any of that's true.

00:40:12.843 --> 00:40:14.512 line:95%,end
All right. Keep protecting her, Leslie.

00:40:14.578 --> 00:40:16.280 line:95%,end
All I'm saying is she
should have been here,

00:40:16.347 --> 00:40:19.083 line:95%,end
but if she was with her mother,
then that's understandable.

00:40:19.150 --> 00:40:21.285 line:95%,end
She said she wasn't coming
back until I was gone.

00:40:21.352 --> 00:40:23.387 line:95%,end
She never mentioned a word about,

00:40:23.454 --> 00:40:26.090 line:95%,end
my mother is sick,
that's why I'm not here.

00:40:26.157 --> 00:40:27.758 line:95%,end
She's not here because I'm here.

00:40:27.825 --> 00:40:30.060 line:95%,end
She said nothing about her mother.

00:40:30.127 --> 00:40:32.296 line:95%,end
GIRLS: [screaming]

00:40:32.363 --> 00:40:34.131 line:95%,end
Woo!

00:40:34.198 --> 00:40:35.366 line:95%,end
WOMEN: [cheering]

00:40:38.702 --> 00:40:40.938 line:95%,end
Good job, honey.

00:40:41.005 --> 00:40:43.507 line:95%,end
HOLLY: That has to feel so good.

00:40:43.574 --> 00:40:47.645 line:95%,end
Can you believe Abby
was not here for one step.

00:40:47.711 --> 00:40:49.146 line:95%,end
How do you guys feel about that?

00:40:49.213 --> 00:40:52.783 line:95%,end
- I miss her.
- I do too.

00:40:58.055 --> 00:40:59.690 line:95%,end
Abby should have been here.

00:40:59.757 --> 00:41:01.225 line:95%,end
She would've been proud of
you guys, but she wasn't.

00:41:01.292 --> 00:41:03.027 line:95%,end
- Uh-huh.
- And it was her choice.

00:41:03.093 --> 00:41:04.995 line:5%,start
[music playing]

